		<title>09BRODICK PRIMARY SCHOOL (1)</title>
		<content>                                       
    Brodick School was built in 1854 on
 land gifted by the Hamilton family for
 educational purposes.  The detached   
 extension was added in 1960 and a     
 classroom hut built in 1975.  A statue
 of the Duke of Hamilton stands in our 
 playground.                           
                                       
    The roll of the school at          
 present is 78, pupils' ages ranging   
 from 5-11 years.  There are four      
 teachers, one our Head Teacher.       
 Specialist teachers in Art, Music,    
 Physical Education and Remedial       
 Education visit our school each week. 
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
